text.tspan: prndev's notes:
I work with Inkscape. I do not know how Illustrator behaves.
All Inkscape Layers are SVG groups.
Inkscape Layer names should be unique.
Inkscape Layer names should be the same as the corresponding SVG group ID (use provided fixup tool to be sure).
All changable style (most notably fill) should be defined in a class.
All conflicting attribute style should be removed (use provided fixup tool to be sure).
All groups with IDs NOT ending in underscore "_", starting with "g" or "XMLID" are exported into separate files.
A single quote ' breaks embedding. Use them to include Twine variables (see README for details).
Original art credit goes to Nov-X.
